<body>
<h1>Game Documentation Change Summary - Ver0.2.4.a</h1>
<p>This summary is based on current source code, README, version log, and side docs</p>
<p>that were moved to <code>docs/unofficial</code>.</p>
<h2>Documentation Layout</h2>
<ul>
<li>Previous loose docs were archived under <code>docs/unofficial/</code>.</li>
<li>Official documentation now lives under <code>docs/official/</code>.</li>
<li>Main universal documentation:</li>
</ul>
<p>  <code>docs/official/game_universal_documentation.md</code></p>
<ul>
<li>Version snapshot:</li>
</ul>
<p>  <code>docs/official/versions/game_doc_ver0.2.4.a.md</code></p>
<ul>
<li>This change summary:</li>
</ul>
<p>  <code>docs/official/versions/game_doc_ver0.2.4.a_change_summary.md</code></p>
<h2>Ver0.2.4.a Scope</h2>
<p>Ver0.2.4.a is a stabilization tag, not a gameplay feature release.</p>
<p>Implemented changes recorded by existing version notes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Version marker updated to <code>0.2.4.a</code>.</li>
<li>Ver0.2.4 diplomacy, structured event log, vassal display, and validation work</li>
</ul>
<p>  are preserved.</p>
<ul>
<li>Repository agent instructions were tightened for future development.</li>
<li>Validation recorded: <code>make</code> passed and all <code>.c/.h</code> files stayed at or below</li>
</ul>
<p>  500 lines.</p>
<p>Gameplay changes in Ver0.2.4.a:</p>
<ul>
<li>None claimed in the side doc.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Ver0.2.4 Stabilization Preserved In This Documentation</h2>
<p>Diplomacy UI:</p>
<ul>
<li>Relation cards now use state-specific templates for peace/tension, war/truce,</li>
</ul>
<p>  and tribute/vassal views.</p>
<ul>
<li>Tense relation return-to-peace thresholds are visible.</li>
</ul>
<p>Vassal display:</p>
<ul>
<li>Tribute display matches actual simulation: 40% of food, livestock, wood,</li>
</ul>
<p>  stone, minerals, and water.</p>
<ul>
<li>Money, population, capacity, and habitability are not tribute.</li>
<li>Army display exposes total soldiers, callable 70%, home guard, current support</li>
</ul>
<p>  use, and support casualties.</p>
<p>Event log:</p>
<ul>
<li>Structured bilingual event entries are the source of truth for new event data.</li>
<li>Snapshot event text and clickable payload now come from the same copied entry.</li>
<li>Historical country chips validate <code>civ_uid</code> before highlighting.</li>
</ul>
<p>Validation:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>--probe-tech10</code> exists and Ver0.2.4 side doc records a successful natural</li>
</ul>
<p>  stage 10 run.</p>
<h2>Documentation Coverage Added</h2>
<p>The new universal documentation covers:</p>
<ul>
<li>Core loop and scheduler.</li>
<li>UI tabs and subtabs.</li>
<li>World generation sliders.</li>
<li>Terrain/geography/climate/ecology/resource tables.</li>
<li>Map rendering, render cache, dirty flags, and RenderSnapshot state.</li>
<li>Natural regions, provinces, cities, capitals, and ports.</li>
<li>Seven civilization metrics and legacy metric caveats.</li>
<li>Technology stages 0-10 and UI.</li>
<li>Expansion, sea lanes, diplomacy, vassals, war.</li>
<li>Population, resources, disorder, plague, collapse.</li>
<li>Event log/debug/performance architecture.</li>
<li>Known technical debt and to-confirm items.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Code / Design Intent Notes</h2>
<ul>
<li>Ver0.2.4.a itself does not claim gameplay behavior changes.</li>
<li>Some README/version-log items describe long-running intended architecture;</li>
</ul>
<p>  the official documentation labels partial areas such as RenderSnapshot</p>
<p>  migration and legacy raw events as implementation state.</p>
<ul>
<li>Older notes mentioned a different direct-vassal governance burden expression</li>
</ul>
<p>  than later README wording. The official doc warns future maintainers to verify</p>
<p>  this directly from <code>src/sim/vassal.c</code> before changing docs or gameplay.</p>
<h2>Future Freeze Checklist</h2>
<p>For the next version freeze:</p>
<ol>
<li>Read <code>docs/official/game_universal_documentation.md</code>.</li>
<li>Read the new source tree and version marker.</li>
<li>Compare git diff from Ver0.2.4.a to the new version.</li>
<li>Copy this version snapshot as the starting point.</li>
<li>Update only behavior that changed in code.</li>
<li>Generate a new version snapshot and change summary.</li>
<li>Mark discrepancies as implemented behavior, intended design, or to-confirm.</li>
</ol>
</body>
</html>
